\par 
\par The drip of water in the bathroom was a compelling distraction.  Dangerous difference, Dasein thought.  Who'll look in on me? he wondered.
\par 
\par It occurred to him to ask himself then who had sounded the alarm.  The breaking window had alerted someone.  The most likely person would be Johnson, the room clerk.  Why would he bring help to the person he was trying to kill?  
