\par 
\par It was an accident, Dasein thought.  It was an accident in a place of dangerous difference.
\par 
\par 
\par Dasein's morning began with a sensation of hunger.  He awoke to cramping pains.  Events of the night flooded into his memory.  His head felt as though it had been kicked from the inside.
\par 
\par Gently, he pushed himself upright.  There was a window directly ahead of him with the green branch of an oak tree across it.  As though his muscles
