\par 
\par The aisle ended in a short flight of wide steps, up to a loading bay with hand trucks racked along its edge.  Jenny led him through a door marked "Office."
\par 
\par It was such an ordinary place -- clips of order forms racked along a wall, two desks with women seated at them typing, a long counter with a gate at one end, windows opening onto the yard and a view of the Inn, a door labeled "Manager" beyond the women.

