\par 
\par "You've been a swimmer on the surface," Piaget said.  "You haven't even seen the struggle.  You haven't yet developed the innocent eye that sees the universe uncluttered by past assumptions.  You were programmed and sent here to break us up."
\par 
\par Dasein paled.
\par 
\par "To be programmed is to be prejudiced," Piaget said.  "Because prejudice is selecting and rejecting and that is programming."  He sighed.  "Such pains we take with you because of our Jenny."
\par 
\par "I came here with an open mind," Dasein said.
\par 
\par "Not prejudiced?"  Piaget raised his eyebrows.
\par 
\par "So you're contending with . . . groups outside over what's the right way . . ."
\par 
\par "Contending is too soft a word, Dasein.  There's a power struggle going on over con
