\par 
\par "You are saying to yourself," Piaget said, "that these fool Santarogans have a psycheletic substance which makes them inhuman."
\par 
\par It was so close to his thoughts that Dasein grew still with fear.  Could they read minds?  Was that a by-product of the Jaspers substance?
\par 
\par "You're equ
ating us with the unwashed, sandaled users of LSD," Piaget said, "Kooks, you would say.  But you are like them -- unaware.  We are aware.  We have truly released the mind.  We have a power medicine -- just as whiskey and gin and aspirin and tobacco . . . 
