\par 
\par "You don't understand," Piaget said.
\par 
\par "But I do understand," Dasein said.  "What'll it be next time?  A gun accident?  How about something heavy dropped from a roof?  Accidentally, of course."  He turned, strode out of the cafe, stood on the sidewalk to study his surroundings.
\par 
\par It was such a n
ormal town.  The trees on the parking strip were so normal.  The young couple walking down the sidewalk across from him -- they were so normal.  The sounds -- a truck out on the avenue to his right, the cars there, a pair of jays arguing in the treetops, 
