\par 
\par The screen door slapped behind him.  Piaget came up to stand at Dasein's side.  "I know what you're thinking," he said.
\par 
\par "Do you, really?"
\par 
\par "I know how all this must look to you."
\par 
\par "Is that so?"
\par 
\par "Believe me," Piaget said, "all this is just a terrible series of coincidences that . . ."
\par 
