\par 
\par Dasein threw back the blankets, swung his feet out.  He motioned Piaget back, sat up.  His feet touched a cold floor.  He took a deep breath, lurched across to the adjoining bed.  His knees felt stronger, but Dasein sensed the shallowness of his reserves.

\par 
