\par 
\par "No need to bother your daughter," Piaget said.  "Run along and . . ."
\par 
\par "But what if . . ."
\par 
\par "There's no danger," Piaget said.
\par 
\par "If you say so," Burdeaux said.  He moved toward the foyer door, paused there a moment to study Dasein, then went out.
\par 
\par "What didn't you want Win to hear?" Dasein asked.
\par 
\par "There he goes again," Piaget said, echoing Burdeaux.
\par 
\par "Something must've . . ."
\par 
\par "There's nothing Win couldn't hear!"
\par 
